<!-- HVAC System Design -->
<h4 class="text-center mt-5">HVAC System Design</h4>
<div class="row justify-content-center text-center mt-4">
  <div class="col-sm-4 mb-3">
    {% include figure.liquid loading="eager" path="assets/projectimages/Fitness Center/L2 - Mechanical.png" title="Transmission drawing" alt="rough drawing" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" style="height: 250px; object-fit: contain;" %}
  </div>
</div>
<div class="text-center caption mt-2 text-muted" style="font-size: 0.9rem;">
  Designed a complete VAV-based HVAC system serving six zones with independently controlled airflow. System components include an air handling unit, supply ductwork, return ductwork, exhaust system, and outdoor air intake. Diffuser placement and duct sizing were determined through engineering calculations referencing ASHRAE 62.1 and ASHRAE 90.1 standards.
</div>

<!-- Engineering Calculations -->
<h4 class="text-center mt-5">Engineering Calculations</h4>
<div class="text-center my-4">
Developed a comprehensive HVAC calculation package including:

- Room-by-room airflow requirements using ACH methodology
- Duct sizing with velocity verification against ASHRAE limits
- Outdoor air compliance verification per ASHRAE 62.1
- Plumbing fixture unit calculations per IPC standards
</div>

<!-- BIM Coordination -->
<h4 class="text-center mt-5">BIM Coordination</h4>
